{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.11",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 11 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:1",
      "text": "Then Zophar the Naamathite answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:2",
      "text": "“Should a multitude of words go unanswered, and a man full of talk be vindicated?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:3",
      "text": "Should your babble silence men, and when you mock, shall no one shame you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:4",
      "text": "For you say, ‘My doctrine is pure, and I am clean in God's eyes.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:5",
      "text": "But oh, that God would speak, and open his lips to you,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:6",
      "text": "and that he would tell you the secrets of wisdom! For he is manifold in understanding. Know then that God exacts of you less than your guilt deserves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:7",
      "text": "“Can you find out the deep things of God? Can you find out the limit of the Almighty?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:8",
      "text": "It is higher than heaven —what can you do? Deeper than Sheol—what can you know?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:9",
      "text": "Its measure is longer than the earth, and broader than the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:10",
      "text": "If he passes through, and imprisons, and calls to judgment, who can hinder him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:11",
      "text": "For he knows worthless men; when he sees iniquity, will he not consider it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:12",
      "text": "But a stupid man will get understanding, when a wild ass's colt is born a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:13",
      "text": "“If you set your heart aright, you will stretch out your hands toward him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:14",
      "text": "If iniquity is in your hand, put it far away, and let not wickedness dwell in your tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:15",
      "text": "Surely then you will lift up your face without blemish; you will be secure, and will not fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:16",
      "text": "You will forget your misery; you will remember it as waters that have passed away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:17",
      "text": "And your life will be brighter than the noonday; its darkness will be like the morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:18",
      "text": "And you will have confidence, because there is hope; you will be protected and take your rest in safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:19",
      "text": "You will lie down, and none will make you afraid; many will entreat your favor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.11.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:20",
      "text": "But the eyes of the wicked will fail; all way of escape will be lost to them, and their hope is to breathe their last.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
